# =============================================================================
# .env.onprem.example — Example env file for the customer-deploy on-prem-
# gateway compose shape (PR #3 scope-doc § decision ii).
#
# CUSTOMER ACTION:
#   1. Copy: cp .env.onprem.example .env
#   2. Fill in the three REQUIRED vars below.
#   3. CRITICAL: echo ".env" >> .gitignore  (warden's customer-side secret-
#      handling pin — do NOT commit your enrollment token to source control).
#   4. docker compose up -d
#
# Tip: do NOT echo $ENROLLMENT_TOKEN — the token is a bearer credential
# until the WSS session takes over (warden pin); shell history is its own
# leak vector.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED — boot fails loud if any of these are unset.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# The WYRE relay endpoint your on-prem-gateway dials.
# Production: wss://relay.wyre.ai
# Staging:    wss://relay.staging.wyre.ai
# MUST be wss:// (assertSecureRelayUrl rejects non-wss at boot).
RELAY_URL=wss://relay.wyre.ai

# Your WYRE-issued enrollment token (short-TTL JWT, default 5 min from issuance).
# Get yours from your WYRE ops contact. They mint via:
#   POST /admin/onprem/enrollment-token (admin-only).
# When the customer portal UI ships post-launch, you'll mint via the portal
# instead. mTLS at M2 Gate A supersedes this token shape entirely.
ENROLLMENT_TOKEN=

# Comma-separated MCP capability slugs your tunnel exposes. BYTE-FOR-BYTE
# match what your enrollment token granted — case-sensitive, no whitespace
# normalization. The structural-validate guard at boot catches obvious
# mismatches; the relay's authoritative check at register-time enforces.
# M2 launch ships with echo-only:
CAPABILITIES=echo

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL — sane defaults; override only if you have a reason.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Log verbosity. debug for first-deploy troubleshooting; info for steady-state.
# LOG_LEVEL=info

# Heartbeat interval to the relay (ms). Default 30000.
# HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS=30000
